<dl id="n09144i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09144i">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09144i"> 144(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> national language</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Current Topics</b> &hellip; With reference to the celebration of St. Patrick&apos;s Day in London, Father O&apos;Farrell writes:&mdash; &ldquo;&hellip; Apart from the &lsquo;O Salutaris&rsquo; and &lsquo;Tantum Ergo&rsquo; at Benediction and the hymn of St Seachnill, &lsquo;Audite Omnes,&rsquo; in honour of St. Patrick, the only language used will be Irish. The Rosary, prayers, hymns and sermon will be in the <mark>National Language</mark>.&hellip;&rdquo; <small> <a name="TL15mar24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#TL15mar24"><cite title="source">The Leader</cite></a> (15 March 1924) 141/1</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
